<subSubSection id="633B138FE651F4A58D0B4C12A20CDC3B" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="112" pageId="32" pageNumber="111" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="E6050A8D6D41C5089D3292806A454D02" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DEFA34F2320E65F1344D3835F473F5D8" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="3A3F0364D0FBA2B39AABF084E20EBF4F" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="91764732AE02EAD0CE7F8C54E6DE40D3" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the type species of 
<taxonomicName id="5C7B6B40102A94120862B22B3349A68D" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="86D06392ADCE46B7CDF6D252A583BA83" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Holopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom, 1845. In the general collection at the NHRS we found more similar specimens under the name &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="68D7F42599419A4BB386B085A8663893" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="E731B15CA0944D4F745745E56CA442E2" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom&quot; with the same labels: 
<normalizedToken id="075C30B178DD67A6D48584C2ACC5BDD5" originalValue="“Rhodus”">&quot;Rhodus&quot;</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="E24A4CEE6EC25070F1122FAA3B17C859" originalValue="“Hedenborg”">&quot;Hedenborg&quot;</normalizedToken>
. They belong to different species. 
<bibRefCitation id="5B223B36AA3705984A0A7E580CA17D31" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Berlingianis, Lund" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.66977" refId="B19" refString="Dahlbom, AG, 1845. Dispositio Methodica Specierum Hymenopterorum, secundum Familias Insectorum Naturales. Part. II. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano. Berlingianis, Lund, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.66977" title="Dispositio Methodica Specierum Hymenopterorum, secundum Familias Insectorum Naturales. Part. II. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano." url="10.5962/bhl.title.66977" year="1845">Dahlbom (1845</bibRefCitation>
: 4) wrote: &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="A92EE87767B8ED01D82D375A52BB8E92" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="8434899D9D8DC3EA1CA63159EB81A167" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nob. ♂ Rhodus rar. 
<emphasis id="4346CC61B651D7E3F3204AA99B76399E" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Hedenborg</emphasis>
&quot;. It is not possible to know how many specimens he examined, but we guess few specimens (
<emphasis id="93344F62268DACB57CECE6A5FB31FA30" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">rar.</emphasis>
), as written in the introduction. Later 
<bibRefCitation id="F1458C1149D43BFC8AA125CEBECD5CAC" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" refId="B21" refString="Dahlbom, AG, 1854. Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta. Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.15890" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta" url="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854</bibRefCitation>
: 53) wrote: &quot; 
<emphasis id="8BACD49A5F9255F9A7F456527D7FA91B" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Duo specimina ex Insula Rhodo vidi, unum a D. Hedenborg alterum a D. Loew lecta</emphasis>
.&quot; The second specimen is not a type, because the material collected by Loew was not included in the original description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A9735163C54350C8EAB54E58E69284C" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="112" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">
The history of the name 
<taxonomicName id="F87BE9971F00E305F38D2253091C8AA6" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="57F6A40A27D686B139BA727E96A59D9D" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">
<pageBreakToken id="5649D225FD4EEE5C07755F42D5E9A037" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" start="start">Holopyga</pageBreakToken>
amoenula
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rather confused, since it was used by many authors to identify almost all the European species of 
<taxonomicName id="66BCE270C0A367008FB15C26B9DA3C2C" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="83B677A0B63A3CFC64B317573AF39320" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The synthesis of this confused situation can be found in 
<bibRefCitation id="D643954767A3CFC681A9011F47B449C4" author="Kimsey, LS" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, New York" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" refId="B37" refString="Kimsey, LS, Bohart, RM, 1991 1990. The Chrysidid Wasps of the World. Oxford University Press, New York" title="The Chrysidid Wasps of the World." year="1991">Kimsey and Bohart (1991</bibRefCitation>
: 225), where many species belonging to different species groups are placed in synonym with 
<taxonomicName id="511EEFD4C31C4A87FE077A95828A65FD" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="82E63B16AFDB99FEDFFACE70C2342FA0" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2792BD5FFBEB22299494493EEA3E064F" author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="Monografie del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Saint-Pierre, Aosta" pageId="47" pageNumber="126" refId="B77" refString="Rosa, P, 2006. I Crisidi della Valle d'Aosta. Monografie del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Saint-Pierre, Aosta" title="I Crisidi della Valle d'Aosta." year="2006">Rosa 2006</bibRefCitation>
: 136). More generally, the most common European species, currently known as 
<taxonomicName id="355EDA997405848EFC56DFF785E7580B" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Forster" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga generosa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="generosa">
<emphasis id="AB75627066E77BC38196B91015F7F106" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga generosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="0E690175BAC723923D785076D8408FCE" originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) (= 
<taxonomicName id="628E66A7841B86E5E783A3C8DD30952B" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="ovata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovata">
<emphasis id="D325428734A1231A75DF5630F3ACB512" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">ovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom, 1854) is found in synonym with 
<taxonomicName id="DCB6CAFC8E96DC75D93BAA2655F737B9" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="3618D9C50E8FB4244E55FFB40EE51F59" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after 
<normalizedToken id="D1F46AF9B9BE5BB048C2887E736435D9" originalValue="Mocsáry’s">Mocsary's</normalizedToken>
monograph (
<bibRefCitation id="C878598CD2098B2A27E3BED0D725B6AE" author="Mocsary, A" journalOrPublisher="Hungarian Academy of Sciences, Budapest" pageId="46" pageNumber="125" refId="B62" refString="Mocsary, A, 1889. Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrestris Universi. Hungarian Academy of Sciences, Budapest" title="Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrestris Universi." year="1889">1889</bibRefCitation>
: 127). The same taxonomical overview was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="12FF7D98D042EDA04D2DF59A8787AE56" author="Mingo, E" journalOrPublisher="HymenopteraChrysididae. Fauna Iberica" pageId="46" pageNumber="125" refId="B56" refString="Mingo, E, 1994. . HymenopteraChrysididae. Fauna Iberica Vol. 6" volume="Vol. 6" year="1994">Mingo (1994</bibRefCitation>
: 73, 204) whereas in the other most important monographs (i.e. 
<bibRefCitation id="080E950C877CFE22BED996673F44E7D6" author="Trautmann, W" journalOrPublisher="Uschman, Weimar" pageId="48" pageNumber="127" refId="B101" refString="Trautmann, W, 1927. Die Goldwespen Europas. Uschman, Weimar" title="Die Goldwespen Europas." year="1927">Trautmann 1927</bibRefCitation>
: 50, and 
<bibRefCitation id="923D220DA1B90B6B0F2F78E9136B138A" author="Berland, L" journalOrPublisher="Faune de France" pageId="43" pageNumber="122" refId="B6" refString="Berland, L, Bernard, F, 1938. Hymenopteres Vespiformes. III. (Cleptidae, Chrysidae [sic], Trigonalidae). Faune de France vol. 34" title="Hymenopteres Vespiformes. III. (Cleptidae, Chrysidae [sic], Trigonalidae)." volume="vol. 34" year="1938">Berland and Bernard 1938</bibRefCitation>
: 42), 
<taxonomicName id="F75B245A56D8B19FA7B5ED9DB2148503" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="583F2A8D9D4196FDF4BAECE04735E09E" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered as variety of 
<taxonomicName id="42DC3FBAF2BEB90995A0848CA5FBEA94" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga gloriosa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriosa">
<emphasis id="F117FE46AF9ECA518D7DF8B12EA55757" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga gloriosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name 
<taxonomicName id="687C61F942111F65CDDA70011AE4E18F" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="gloriosa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriosa">
<emphasis id="F4ED5FF0CAC63D792B83761A89CDCD06" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">gloriosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius has been suppressed by the ICZN Commission (
<bibRefCitation id="CB4E353ADDD38C89ABAC1CB6CF5F0ABF" author="ICZN" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" pagination="194 - 196" refId="B34" refString="ICZN, 1998. Opinion 1906: Euchroeus Latreille, 1809 (Insecta, Hymenoptera): conserved; Chrysis purpurata Fabricius, 1787 (currently Euchroeus purpuratus): specific name conserved; and Chrysis gloriosa Fabricius, 1793: specific name supressed. Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature 55 (3): 194 - 196" title="Opinion 1906: Euchroeus Latreille, 1809 (Insecta, Hymenoptera): conserved; Chrysis purpurata Fabricius, 1787 (currently Euchroeus purpuratus): specific name conserved; and Chrysis gloriosa Fabricius, 1793: specific name supressed." volume="55" year="1998">ICZN 1998</bibRefCitation>
, Opinion 1906) and the species previously identified with this name 
<emphasis id="72E2258A4FE0EF82FCEB55A3F12F648D" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">sensu</emphasis>
Linsenmaier are related with a different species-group, which includes 
<taxonomicName id="67F6E4C3CFDC07B75DD838646B8056C8" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Lepeletier" baseAuthorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga lucida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucida">
<emphasis id="184CF7677429957E55C5EBB8E9625626" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga lucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lepeletier), 
<taxonomicName id="A0CBB515BCF1DAEC4561E3BCE9B7936C" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Forster" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga inflammata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflammata">
<emphasis id="43ABFBB0F618A0C25682397BBD96B934" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga inflammata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="56831E03ABC5B86A553B2D35D4B8FBDD" originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
), 
<taxonomicName id="53B63A986EE330437E5001886335B15F" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga caucasica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis id="22761C22882E8F9E034C5E0DC2D0A032" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="C5CB984E05FA50FEDBB222A9144E9594" originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
, etc.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B93AC6FB3C7BA2CE10C39B11C833EA37" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">
Only after 
<normalizedToken id="A316C1A14E45BD239E10E3CCDF52496E" originalValue="Linsenmaier’s">Linsenmaier's</normalizedToken>
revision (
<bibRefCitation id="AE3671DE9473DD2E57F49EC6382B65E8" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 232" refId="B45" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1959. Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 32 (1): 1 - 232" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies." volume="32" year="1959">1959</bibRefCitation>
) of the European species, 
<taxonomicName id="E5CA128A47CDC663CD8AD108DE97C461" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="11EC564D587616F82AB8BB9A8719D21D" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was correctly identified and recognized as a distinct, valid species endemic to Rhodes. The discussion on the name 
<taxonomicName id="DBCA5D9A4C8F52F5E579DDD90F80322A" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="18BF59919F352249087F6C10C0875DDE" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
originates in 
<normalizedToken id="EAFE1DB728F77DFD5A5FAE2AFA5BDCAD" originalValue="Dahlbom’s">Dahlbom's</normalizedToken>
monograph (
<bibRefCitation id="FC8D0A2BD0EAADE22F72A106CFE61D66" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" refId="B21" refString="Dahlbom, AG, 1854. Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta. Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.15890" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta" url="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" year="1854">1854</bibRefCitation>
: 53). Dahlbom considered 
<taxonomicName id="9F03D3046C2C99925B9BFDB1DAAFF0BE" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="F097214DB920AF21CF9E3C6A4E6504A7" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as variety (var. d) of the new described species 
<taxonomicName id="5182F5498B8AEB2D556D448880909053" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga ovata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovata">
<emphasis id="64A1AC19B996F04105B9F3250B9FD98B" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga ovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, contrary to the Principle of Priority that was not yet applied at that time. Two subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="1E1CEE005D207C4471BFF457DCC50BA5" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="CCFCFB276A5CBCB3952B231BDD2BF57F" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are present in southern Europe: 
<taxonomicName id="CA69E9113BA08CA651DD64EF602C27D1" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Linsenmaier" authorityYear="1959" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula subsp. oriensa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="amoenula" subSpecies="oriensa">Holopyga amoenula ssp. oriensa</taxonomicName>
Linsenmaier and 
<taxonomicName id="3D76FDCA4326AA232B4385C46A321C71" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Linsenmaier" authorityYear="1959" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="subsp. occidenta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="amoenula" subSpecies="occidenta">ssp. occidenta</taxonomicName>
Linsenmaier. The possibility that they could be valid species should be taken in consideration.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9FD00E8B7F86DD9F863D612D2BC5A25F" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">
Since there are different specimens in the collection, and species collected by Hedenborg on Rhodes under the name 
<taxonomicName id="2929E59FBC9D46F6AA5742C8A66C8449" authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis id="B63A82D34DA9F97D8F6584552B4CE88F" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we hereby designate as the lectotype the specimen which match the current interpretation of the species. It is pinned, in perfect condition and we dissected the genitalia, glued with the specimen (Plate 
<figureCitation id="7A05074EC00A52AA730BB01720430226" captionStart="Plate 29" captionStartId="F29" captionText="Plate 29. Holopyga amoenula Dahlbom, 1845, lectotype (photo HV). A Habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C metasoma, lateral view." pageId="33" pageNumber="112">29</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
